          <name>AUXILIARY_IMAGE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 1</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Overlays the auxiliary image on top of an NPatch image. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>The resulting visual image will be at least as large as the smallest possible n-patch or the auxiliary image, whichever is larger.</para>
<para>Name &quot;auxiliaryImage&quot;, Type Property::STRING, URL of the image. <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default true </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589ad6eb318a936183a1c8cd9dd7404f7b88" prot="public">
          <name>AUXILIARY_IMAGE_ALPHA</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 2</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>An alpha value for mixing between the masked main NPatch image and the auxiliary image. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;auxiliaryImageAlpha&quot;, Type Property::FLOAT, between 0 and 1 <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default 0 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a88d26887c93757d33f184d20519c355a" prot="public">
          <name>LOOP_COUNT</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 3</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The number of times the AnimatedImageVisual or AnimatedVectorImageVisual will be looped. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;loopCount&quot;, type Property::INTEGER. <simplesect kind="note"><para>For Animated images only. Default -1. if &lt; 0, loop unlimited. else, loop loopCount times. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589ac58ce8efefe479a7115f04cc004e0d14" prot="public">
          <name>PLAY_RANGE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 4</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The playing range the AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Animation will play between the values specified. The array can have two integer values. Or it can have one or two strings, which are markers. More will be ignored. Both values should be between 0 and the total frame number, otherwise they will be ignored. If the range provided is not in proper order ( minimum, maximum ), it will be reordered.</para>
<para>A marker has its start frame and end frame. Animation will play between the start frame and the end frame of the marker if one marker is specified. Or animation will play between the start frame of the first marker and the end frame of the second marker if two markers are specified.</para>
<para>Name &quot;playRange&quot;, Type Property::ARRAY of Property::INTEGER or Property::ARRAY of Property::STRING or Property::STRING (one marker). <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default 0 and the total frame number. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a1d3a682484f2ff9708d9785f0a996f46" prot="public">
          <name>PLAY_STATE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 5</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The playing state the AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;playState&quot;, Type <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1PlayState_1aed5ec28059134a04d402a812460c1688" kindref="member">PlayState::Type</ref> (Property::INTEGER) <simplesect kind="note"><para>This property is read-only. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a26f77b7af25b1105759690b9c2f61b52" prot="public">
          <name>CURRENT_FRAME_NUMBER</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 6</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The current frame number the AnimatedImageVisual and AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;currentFrameNumber&quot;, Type Property::INTEGER, between [0, the maximum frame number] or between the play range if specified <simplesect kind="note"><para>This property is read-only. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a22b00b39670922bf7a6c8f95302ce742" prot="public">
          <name>TOTAL_FRAME_NUMBER</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 7</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The total frame number the AnimatedImageVisual and AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;totalFrameNumber&quot;, Type Property::INTEGER. <simplesect kind="note"><para>This property is read-only. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589aa026730713c9a9662d858abb071464d6" prot="public">
          <name>STOP_BEHAVIOR</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 8</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The stop behavior the AnimatedImageVisual and AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;stopBehavior&quot;, Type <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1StopBehavior_1a3170d5c2e44903c05d38579de756410a" kindref="member">StopBehavior::Type</ref> (Property::INTEGER) <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default value is <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1StopBehavior_1a3170d5c2e44903c05d38579de756410aabd280ffd1773a7bf7097b04a230478d3" kindref="member">StopBehavior::CURRENT_FRAME</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a46e10cd21bbc05be651e8f4a284685e7" prot="public">
          <name>LOOPING_MODE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 9</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The looping mode the AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;loopingMode&quot;, Type <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1LoopingMode_1af416767cee5a21d16a3901c62df95642" kindref="member">LoopingMode::Type</ref> (Property::INTEGER) <simplesect kind="note"><para>Default value is <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1LoopingMode_1af416767cee5a21d16a3901c62df95642a90d24f35161d3602cf9a08708de01fbc" kindref="member">LoopingMode::RESTART</ref>. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589ad81c4b767a5f211d9ee9b7e9e0868e09" prot="public">
          <name>CONTENT_INFO</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 10</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The content information the AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Type Property::MAP. The map contains the layer name as a key and Property::Array as a value. And the array contains 2 integer values which are the frame numbers, the start frame number and the end frame number of the layer. <simplesect kind="note"><para>This property is read-only. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a637ba606e545e3699e9d0eff04f2b569" prot="public">
          <name>REDRAW_IN_SCALING_DOWN</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 11</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to redraw the image when the visual is scaled down. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;redrawInScalingDown&quot;, type Property::BOOLEAN. <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used in the AnimatedVectorImageVisual. The default is true. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589ac3c6373d91e3573d77e980c46ab193e9" prot="public">
          <name>MASKING_TYPE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 12</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to apply mask in loading time or rendering time. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;maskingType&quot;, type <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1PlayState_1aed5ec28059134a04d402a812460c1688" kindref="member">PlayState::Type</ref> (Property::INTEGER). In general, MASKING_ON_LOADING is the default behavior. However, if the visual uses an external texture, only MASKING_ON_RENDERING is possible. So we change its value to MASKING_ON_RENDERING even if the visual sets the MASKING_TYPE as MASKING_ON_LOADING when it uses external texture. <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used in the <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1ImageVisual" kindref="compound">ImageVisual</ref> and AnimatedImageVisual. The default is MASKING_ON_LOADING. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589aea67f95aa20afa3fb68e52ba8281fdad" prot="public">
          <name>FAST_TRACK_UPLOADING</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 13</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>If true, uploads texture before ResourceReady signal is emitted. Otherwise uploads after texture load is completed. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;fastTrackUploading&quot;, type Property::BOOLEAN If true, the upload happens without event-thread dependency, but the following need to be considered:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Texture size is not valid until upload is fully complete.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Texture cannot be cached (a new image is uploaded every time).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Seamless visual change is not supported.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>The following, if set are also not supported and will be ignored:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Alpha masking</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Synchronous loading</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Reload action</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Custom shader <simplesect kind="note"><para>Used by the <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1ImageVisual" kindref="compound">ImageVisual</ref>. The default is false. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a32f235ef14530ed03e1f25ce310c6ea8" prot="public">
          <name>ENABLE_BROKEN_IMAGE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 14</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to enable broken image in image visual. Some of visual don&apos;t need to show broken image(ex. placeholder) Disable broken image for these visuals. default is true. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This property is write-only. Only be used for <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1ImageView" kindref="compound">ImageView</ref> internal. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a1e0e5f7c6c95450ec9c114007fcc6db2" prot="public">
          <name>MARKER_INFO</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 15</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>The marker information the AnimatedVectorImageVisual will use. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Type Property::MAP. The map contains the marker name as a key and Property::Array as a value. And the array contains 2 integer values which are the frame numbers, the start frame number and the end frame number of the marker. <simplesect kind="note"><para>This property is read-only. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589ab4c83824f7a1965c262072b37b469aca" prot="public">
          <name>ENABLE_FRAME_CACHE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 16</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to AnimatedVectorImageVisual fixed cache or not. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;enableFrameCache&quot;, type Property::BOOLEAN. If this property is true, AnimatedVectorImageVisual enable frame cache for loading and keeps loaded frame until the visual is removed. It reduces CPU cost when the animated image will be looping. But it can spend a lot of memory if the resource has high resolution image or many frame count. <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used in the AnimatedVectorImageVisual. The default is false </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a83b6c60f16024079bfb4ae465f0e8c18" prot="public">
          <name>NOTIFY_AFTER_RASTERIZATION</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 17</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether notify AnimatedVectorImageVisual to render thread after every rasterization or not. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;notifyAfterRasterization&quot;, type Property::BOOLEAN. If this property is true, AnimatedVectorImageVisual send notify to render thread after every rasterization. If false, AnimatedVectorImageVisual set Renderer&apos;s Behaviour as Continouly (mean, always update the render thread.)</para>
<para>This flag is useful if given resource has low fps, so we don&apos;t need to render every frame. <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used in the AnimatedVectorImageVisual. The default is false. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a138c2a26fc6f51845260dbc88483f1b1" prot="public">
          <name>SYNCHRONOUS_SIZING</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 18</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to synchronize image texture size to visual size. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;synchronousSizing&quot;, type Property::BOOLEAN. If this property is true, <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1ImageVisual" kindref="compound">ImageVisual</ref> ignores mDesiredSize. <simplesect kind="note"><para>Used by the <ref refid="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1ImageVisual" kindref="compound">ImageVisual</ref>. The default is false. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a62f238292eb03208f879774ec8b8961f" prot="public">
          <name>FRAME_SPEED_FACTOR</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 19</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Specifies a speed factor for the animated image frame. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;frameSpeedFactor&quot;, type Property::FLOAT.</para>
<para>The speed factor is a multiplier of the normal velocity of the animation. Values between [0,1] will slow down the animation and values above one will speed up the animation.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>The range of this value is clamped between [0.01f ~ 100.0f]. It might be supported out of bound, and negative value in future. </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used in the AnimatedImageVisual and AnimatedVectorImageVisual. The default is 1.0f. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589ac287ca16101bc3604ab579853a11f940" prot="public">
          <name>REDRAW_IN_SCALING_UP</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 20</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Whether to redraw the image when the visual is scaled up. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;redrawInScalingUp&quot;, type Property::BOOLEAN. <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used in the AnimatedVectorImageVisual. The default is true. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
        <enumvalue id="namespaceDali_1_1Ui_1_1DevelImageVisual_1_1Property_1aa05797934af169cdcac6cee86b7a4589a87e978e988e6dac53ae30d1ff17eaee8" prot="public">
          <name>RENDER_SCALE</name>
          <initializer>= ORIENTATION_CORRECTION + 21</initializer>
          <briefdescription>
<para>Renders a texture at a given scale. </para>
          </briefdescription>
          <detaileddescription>
<para>Name &quot;renderScale&quot;, type Property::FLOAT. Using render scale with Actor::Property::SCALE(= mRedrawInScalingUp is true) may scale twice. i.e RENDER_SCALE = 1.5f and SCALE = 2.0f would eventually multiply the texture by 3.0f <simplesect kind="note"><para>It is used when scaling up AnimatedVectorImageVisual. The default is 1.0f. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
          </detaileddescription>
        </enumvalue>
